description:
Welcome to Marion Street in Bedstuy! We are long time Brooklyn residents, but recently moved to this block where we have been slowly restoring this beautiful dream home. Lauren and I are both friendly and social. We are excited to host you and share our NYC experience - a city we both love. We use AirBnB on our travels and understand what it takes to be a great host.

Over the past few months we have been restoring this beautiful home.  

Your private space is the garden level of a brick- brownstone with plenty of day light throughout.  We live upstairs should you have any questions.
Your bedroom is over looking the backyard garden. There's an outdoor space with reclaimed brick patio. 
Original details throughout: tin ceilings, plaster moldings, wood panel doors, original floors.

Renovated kitchen and bath with a towel warmer.
Washer and dryer.
Large closets.

The daybed in the living room can accommodate one person.  We also have a Japanese buckwheat floor mattress should you need it.

Fresh linens and towels provided. 100% cotton. 

J train at Chauncey St, A/C train at Rockaway Ave, L train at Bushwick Ave/Aberdeen.  We are very accessible to all parts of NYC.

Once your reservation is confirmed, please check back as other information becomes available (e.g. WiFi password, detailed directions, and check-out procedure).

Please feel at home.  You have access to the backyard garden.  Your space also has a private kitchen and living room to read or watch TV.  There's also a washer and dryer on site.

We are accommodating to our guests. We will respect your space; however, we are more than happy to provide any information should you need it.

Marion Street is a Brooklyn gem!

We live on a quiet tree lined block with a new and well maintained city park across the street.
Jazz festival and other community activities organized by a strong block association.
Mentioned as one of the "Greenest Blocks in Brooklyn" by the Brooklyn Botanical Garden.

To be near a subway line is nice, but to be within a few short blocks of 3 subway lines is better!  Airports, Brooklyn and Manhattan sites could not be more accessible.

We are a 1 minute walk to the J train, a 5 min walk to the A/C train, and a 10 min walk to the L train. 

Both the J and A/C trains go directly to and from JFK airport.

hosts.about:
Hi,

My name is Anthony.  Born in the Philippines, raised in Chicago and have been living in NYC for the past 6 years.  By day, I work as an automation engineer at a human genetics center.  I enjoy NYC and take full advantage of all that it has to offer: culture, arts, restaurants, music, sports, etc... 

Lauren hails from Philadelphia and has been living in Brooklyn for the past 16 years!  She is a photographer by trade.  She is an animal lover, is a people person, and has a voracious appetite to live life to the fullest. 

We can't wait to share our experience of the best that NYC has to offer!

review.comments:
Merci à Lauren et Anthony qui nous ont accueillis chaleureusement malgré un retard conséquent ....
L'appartement est très confortable spacieux lumineux et bien décoré on se sent tout de suite chez soi....
Le petit jardin derrière est adorable 
La rue à la sortie de l'arrêt de métro est moche et sale mais dès qu'on la traverse cette mauvaise impression disparait 
dès qu'on découvre ces jolies brownstones bordant des rues tranquilles 
Allez y c'est un New york authentique !!
